The paper discusses entity linking and disambiguation, which are tasks commonly studied in the information retrieval (cs.IR), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) communities. The paper also mentions the use of knowledge bases (KBs), which are often studied in the databases (cs.DB) community. Finally, the paper proposes a human-in-the-loop approach, which involves user feedback and engagement, suggesting a potential connection to the machine learning (cs.LG) community.
